<span id="freeTextContainer15977241082479378701">Powerful and precise as all of the essays are, Baldwin hits his stride with the titular piece, in which he embeds personal meditations on his father&apos;s death into a social analysis of the Harlem riot of 1943 and race relations in America. There&apos;s nothing else quite like it in the collection, though the essays about Paris in the third and final section are almost as brilliant.</span>
  <span id="freeText15977241082479378701" style="display:none">Powerful and precise as all of the essays are, Baldwin hits his stride with the titular piece, in which he embeds personal meditations on his father's death into a social analysis of the Harlem riot of 1943 and race relations in America. There's nothing else quite like it in the collection, though the essays about Paris in the third and final section are almost as brilliant.</span>
