</div>

    </div>
  </div>
    <div class="elementListBrownSeparator"></div>



  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3703650056" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3703650056" />
    <a title="Puck" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18562856-puck"><img alt="Puck" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498403772p2/18562856.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3703650056?book_show_action=true">Dec 23, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Puck" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Puck" href="/user/show/18562856-puck">Puck</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780241334003" href="/book/show/35997466-notes-of-a-native-son">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18562856-puck?shelf=biography">biography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18562856-puck?shelf=people-of-colour">people-of-colour</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18562856-puck?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3703650056" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1614715967447446281"><b>
  <i> “The time has come to realize that the interracial drama acted out on the American continent has not only created a new black man, it has created a new white man, too.&quot; </i>
</b><br/><br/>Baldwin is a razor-sharp author with such a compelling voice: I underline many sentences while reading his novels. However, this essay-collection feels a bit like a mixed bag. <br/>The essays in Part 1 are more reflections on contemporary black movies and books: interesting, but they don&apos;t linger. Part 2 gave insight in Baldwin&apos;s</span>
  <span id="freeText1614715967447446281" style="display:none"><b>
  <i> “The time has come to realize that the interracial drama acted out on the American continent has not only created a new black man, it has created a new white man, too." </i>
</b><br /><br />Baldwin is a razor-sharp author with such a compelling voice: I underline many sentences while reading his novels. However, this essay-collection feels a bit like a mixed bag. <br />The essays in Part 1 are more reflections on contemporary black movies and books: interesting, but they don't linger. Part 2 gave insight in Baldwin's personal life, and 'Notes of a Native Son' was especially touching if you have read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17143.Go_Tell_It_on_the_Mountain" title="Go Tell It on the Mountain by James Baldwin" rel="nofollow noopener">Go Tell It on the Mountain</a>.<br /><br />Part 3 however, is a collection of essays Baldwin wrote in Paris or looking back on his time living there, and those to me were the most impressive. <br />Being in Europe made him not only reflect on his identity as a Black American, but also how it differs from the identity of Black Europeans. Europe's colonial past is unlike the history of slavery in America, and yet the world will see no difference between two black men. Baldwin's reflection on how that generalization makes him feel strikes deep. <br /><br />A thoughful series of essays, not all hitting the mark, but all well-written. <b>3,5 stars.</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="1614715967447446281" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

